Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
  int temperature;
  bool isRaining;

  WeatherSimulator(int initialTemp) {
    temperature = initialTemp;
    isRaining = false;
  }

  void updateWeather() {
    if (temperature < 20) {
      isRaining = true;
    } else {
      isRaining = false;
    }
  }

  void changeTemperature(int newTemp) {
    temperature = newTemp;
    this.updateWeather();
  }
}",

If an observer sees that it had stopped raining, can they intervene and deduce the exact previous temperature?
